setIgnoreDupResponses

public void setIgnoreDupResponses(javax.el.ValueExpression __ignoreDupResponses)
Attribute allows you to ignore an Ajax response produced by a request if the newest 'similar' request is in the queue already. ignoreDupResponses="true" does not cancel the request while it is processed on the server, but just allows avoiding unnecessary updates on the client side if the response isn't actual now Setter for ignoreDupResponses

Parameters:
ignoreDupResponses - - new value

setSizeExceededBehavior

public void setSizeExceededBehavior(javax.el.ValueExpression __sizeExceededBehavior)
Defines the strategies of the queue's behavior if the number of the requests waiting in the queue is exceeded. There are four strategies: dropNext (by default), dropNew, fireNext , fireNew. Setter for sizeExceededBehavior

Parameters:
sizeExceededBehavior - - new value
